README.md
     1â†’# Versioning Library for Go
     2â†’
     3â†’![Build Status](https://github.com/hashicorp/go-version/actions/workflows/go-tests.yml/badge.svg)
     4â†’[![Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/badge/github.com/hashicorp/go-version.svg)](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version)
     5â†’
     6â†’go-version is a library for parsing versions and version constraints,
     7â†’and verifying versions against a set of constraints. go-version
     8â†’can sort a collection of versions properly, handles prerelease/beta
     9â†’versions, can increment versions, etc.
    10â†’
    11â†’Versions used with go-version must follow [SemVer](http://semver.org/).
    12â†’
    13â†’## Installation and Usage
    14â†’
    15â†’Package documentation can be found on
    16â†’[Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version).
    17â†’
    18â†’Installation can be done with a normal `go get`:
    19â†’
    20â†’```
    21â†’$ go get github.com/hashicorp/go-version
    22â†’```
    23â†’
    24â†’#### Version Parsing and Comparison
    25â†’
    26â†’```go
    27â†’v1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    28â†’v2, err := version.NewVersion("1.5+metadata")
    29â†’
    30â†’// Comparison example. There is also GreaterThan, Equal, and just
    31â†’// a simple Compare that returns an int allowing easy >=, <=, etc.
    32â†’if v1.LessThan(v2) {
    33â†’    fmt.Printf("%s is less than %s", v1, v2)
    34â†’}
    35â†’```
    36â†’
    37â†’#### Version Constraints
    38â†’
    39â†’```go
    40â†’v1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    41â†’
    42â†’// Constraints example.
    43â†’constraints, err := version.NewConstraint(">= 1.0, < 1.4")
    44â†’if constraints.Check(v1) {
    45â†’	fmt.Printf("%s satisfies constraints %s", v1, constraints)
    46â†’}
    47â†’```
    48â†’
    49â†’#### Version Sorting
    50â†’
    51â†’```go
    52â†’versionsRaw := []string{"1.1", "0.7.1", "1.4-beta", "1.4", "2"}
    53â†’versions := make([]*version.Version, len(versionsRaw))
    54â†’for i, raw := range versionsRaw {
    55â†’    v, _ := version.NewVersion(raw)
    56â†’    versions[i] = v
    57â†’}
    58â†’
    59â†’// After this, the versions are properly sorted
    60â†’sort.Sort(version.Collection(versions))
    61â†’```
    62â†’
    63â†’## Issues and Contributing
    64â†’
    65â†’If you find an issue with this library, please report an issue. If you'd
    66â†’like, we welcome any contributions. Fork this library and submit a pull
    67â†’request.
